The article celebrates Easter Sunday, a day of hope and joy, renewal, and rebirth for Christians worldwide. It signifies the end of Lent, a period of sacrifice and contemplation, and commemorates Christ's Resurrection, reminding people of God's love and the promise of redemption. During Lent, the focus was on those suffering from various hardships such as violence, persecution, grief, isolation, illness, and poverty. The article emphasizes the Easter message that nothing, not even death, can surpass the power of faith, hope, and love. It encourages people to remember Jesus' sacrifice and to love God and their neighbors, treating one another with compassion. The author extends Easter blessings to those gathering in churches and homes and wishes them a happy Easter.